\section{Appendix A: Methodology}
\noindent The information in this report was primarily generated using the Qualys Web Application Scanning tool. The discovery scan uses the provided domains, subdomains, and URLs and will crawl the links and attempt to find other resources and lower level domains in order to provide a complete view of the entire web application. Once the entire view of the web application is established, a vulnerability scan is performed.

\noindent The Vulnerability scan utilizes Qualys plugins, or QIDs. These are individual tests which will use various means, such as making certain HTTP requests or checking for specific responses or information contained in the response to determine if a web application contains a specific vulnerability. Qualys maintains and extensive database of these QIDs and makes additions and updates on a regular basis. All of the QIDs pertaining to web application scanning are used in the vulnerability scanning portion of the scan.

\noindent Once the vulnerability scan is complete, a report is generated which contains all of the results of the testing and any vulnerabilities found to be present based on the results of the QID testing. These results range in severity from Minimal (Level 1) to Urgent (Level 5). Table 1 below gives a detailed description of the different vulnerability levels and their potential consequences. There are also some findings which are labelled as Information Gathered. These are findings that are not necessarily classified as vulnerabilities, but consist of various information that was seen in the course of testing. Some information gathered is simply information about the scan, the links crawled and found, and so forth and some information gathered could be the existence of information about the web application that you may or may not want available to the general public, but can be found using the methods of the scan. It is a good idea to review all vulnerabilities and information gathered and determine the best course of action to mitigate the vulnerabilities and make sure the information disclosed is only the information that you wish to be disclosed. The detailed vulnerability findings and suggestions are contained in Appendix C: Attachments.
